author: Gordon Peterson
comment: Now I have had looper since it started and it's gone up to 20 dollars a year. Any thought being given to lifetime looper benefits? I would rather pay 100 one time than have to pay 20 per year. Even if it is a limited time offer. Looper is not necessary for a high handicapper but for a 10 or below it's a very useful tool. That guy who said it cut ten strokes wouldn't lie and I would love to play him for a looper membership.

reply.author: Swing by Swing Golf GPS
reply.content: Thank you for your suggestion, it will be forwarded on to management.  FYI, the Looper upgrade is offered throughout the year at a sale price.  Keep an eye out and you will be able to purchase it and save a few dollars.  We hear from looper users both high and low handicap how looper helps their game.  One user lowered his handicap by 10 strokes.

EDIT: Cancelled my Looper subscription because it got too expensive. Also it kept asking for a review every time even though I'd left one. (dropped my score from 5 to 3 stars)

author: Chris Parkinson
comment: My GPS has stopped working. Google maps tells me where I am and my other golf app. is correct but this app.l tells me I am not on the tee so distances are not shown. Why?????

reply.author: Swing by Swing Golf GPS
reply.content: Chris, please check in your phone settings under location that it is turned on and set for high accuracy.  If not please change to that and try the app again.  If those settings are correct, then please contact us at support@swingbyswing.com and we will be glad to help you.
